        },
        {
            "id": 1,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "Multilayer networks proved to be suitable in extracting and providing dependency information of different complex systems . <S>",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "The construction of these networks is difficult",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "and is mostly done with a static approach ,",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "neglecting time delayed interdependences . <S>",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "Tensors are objects",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "that naturally represent multilayer networks",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "and in this paper , we propose a new methodology",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "based on Tucker tensor autoregression",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "in order to build a multilayer network directly from data . <S>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "This methodology captures within and between connections across layers",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "and makes use of a filtering procedure",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 11,
            "text": "to extract relevant information",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 12,
            "text": "and improve visualization . <S>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "We show the application of this methodology to different stationary fractionally differenced financial data . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 16,
            "text": "We argue",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 16,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "that our result is useful to understand the dependencies across three different aspects of financial risk ,",
            "relation": "FINDINGS"
        },
        {
            "id": 17,
            "parent": 16,
            "text": "namely market risk , liquidity risk , and volatility risk . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 18,
            "parent": 19,
            "text": "Indeed , we show",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 19,
            "parent": 16,
            "text": "how the resulting visualization is a useful tool for risk managers",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 20,
            "parent": 19,
            "text": "depicting dependency asymmetries between different risk factors",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 21,
            "parent": 20,
            "text": "and accounting for delayed cross dependencies . <S>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 22,
            "parent": 19,
            "text": "The constructed multilayer network shows a strong interconnection between the volumes and prices layers across all the stocks considered",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
